HEADWORD: Spermist
<hw>Sperm"ist</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Biol.)</fld> <def>A
believer in the doctrine, formerly current, of encasement in the male
(see <er>Encasement</er>), in which the seminal thread, or spermatozoid,
was considered as the real animal germ, the head being the true animal
head and the tail the body.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

